{"embedding_dim": 1536, "data": [{"__id__": "chunk-2609d28a699c4fb0f3d8f329ec8865c4", "__created_at__": 1773645846, "content": "Table source7.Artist_Encyclopedia is about: The Artist_Encyclopedia.csv table contains musician profiles with Wikidata identifiers, birth dates, names, number of children, websites, residences, ethnicities, religions, start of activity dates, Twitter and Genius names, and record labels.\nIt contains the following columns:\n- musician (object): Wikidata entity identifier for the musician. Samples: ['http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q6096', 'http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q5977', 'http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q8349']\n- birthDate (object): Date of birth of the musician. Samples: ['1971-10-20T00:00:00Z', '1936-09-07T00:00:00Z', '1959-10-23T00:00:00Z']\n- familyNameLabel (object): Family name of the musician. Samples: ['Broadus', 'Holley', 'Yankovic']\n- givenNameLabel (object): Given name of the musician. Samples: ['Cordozar', 'Hardin', 'Alfred']\n- numberOfChildren (float64): Number of children the musician has. Samples: [4.0]\n- websiteLabel (object): Official website of the musician. Samples: ['http://snoopdogg.com/', 'http://www.buddyholly.com', 'http://weirdal.com/']\n- residenceLabel (object): City where the musician resides. Samples: ['Del Mar']\n- ethnicityLabel (object): Ethnicity of the musician. Samples: ['African Americans', 'African Americans']\n- religionLabel (object): Religion of the musician. Samples: ['Islam', 'Baptists', 'Christianity']\n- activityStart (object): Year the musician started their career. Samples: ['1991-01-01T00:00:00Z', '1952-01-01T00:00:00Z', '1976-01-01T00:00:00Z']\n- twitterNameLabel (object): Twitter username of the artist. Samples: ['snoopdogg', 'alyankovic', 'tomdelonge']\n- geniusNameLabel (object): Artist name formatted for Genius platform. Samples: ['Snoop-dogg', 'Buddy-holly', 'Weird-al-yankovic']\n- recordLabelLabel (object): Record label of the artist. Samples: ['Death Row Records', 'Brunswick', 'Volcano Entertainment']\n\n===\n\nTable source8.Performer_Registry is about: The Performer_Registry.csv table contains musician details including unique Wikidata IDs, names, gender, birth dates, cities, and family information. It also includes parents' names, spouse, number of children, musical kind, and personal webpages.\nIt contains the following columns:\n- musicianID (object): Wikidata entity identifier for the musician. Samples: ['http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q6096', 'http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q5977', 'http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q8349']\n- musicianName (object): Name of the musician, possibly including IPI numbers. Samples: ['Bigg Snoop Dogg', '00085469927 IPI', 'Al Yankovic']\n- genderType (object): Gender of the musician (m for male). Samples: ['m', 'm', 'm']\n- birthDate (object): Date of birth of the musician. Samples: ['1971-10-20T00:00:00Z', '1936-09-07T00:00:00Z', '1959-10-23T00:00:00Z']\n- city (object): City where the musician was born. Samples: ['Long Beach', 'Lubbock', 'Downey']\n- familyName (object): Last name of the musician. Samples: ['Broadus', 'Holley', 'Yankovic']\n- forename (object): First name of the musician. Samples: ['Cordozar', 'Hardin', 'Alfred']\n- fatherName (object): Name of the musician's father. Samples: ['Nick Louis Yankovic']\n- motherName (object): Name of the musician's mother. Samples: ['Mary Yankovic']\n- spouse (object): Name of the musician's spouse. Samples: ['Maria Elena Holly', 'Suzanne Yankovic', 'Lil Hardin Armstrong']\n- NChildren (float64): Number of children the performer has. Samples: [4.0]\n- kind (object): Type of performance or genre associated with the performer. Samples: ['African-American music', 'rock and roll', 'humor']\n- webpage (object): Official website URL of the performer. Samples: ['http://snoopdogg.com/', 'http://www.buddyholly.com', 'http://weirdal.com/']", "full_doc_id": "doc-2609d28a699c4fb0f3d8f329ec8865c4", "file_path": "unknown_source", "vector": ""}], "matrix": ""}